&gt; I want to be able to either use textui or swingui to call my set of
&gt; tests, so I have the following:

if you want that your tests share a property (like the url), you can use 
the PropertyManager of the JUnit-addons library.  In your case, you can 
register a new property at startup and call it in the test&#39;s setup:

public class MyTest extends TestCase {

   private SoapClient client;

   protected void setUp() throws Exception {
      String url = PropertyManager.getProperty(&quot;url-key&quot;);
      client = SoapClient.getInstance(url);
      client.setKeepAlive(true);
   }

   public void testXYZ() {
   }

   public static void main(String[] args) {
      PropertyManager.setProperty(&quot;url-key&quot;, args[0]);
      junit.swingui.TestRunner.run(MyTest.class);
   }

But of course you&#39;ll have to install JUnit-addons 
&lt;http://junit-addons.sf.net&gt;

-Vladimir

